Topic: OIR Test (Verbal Reasoning)

Today we will learn the first actual test in SSB screening.

1️⃣ What is OIR Test?

The Officer Intelligence Rating (OIR) test checks your basic intelligence and logical thinking speed.

It contains verbal and non-verbal reasoning questions.

📊 Structure

Section	Questions	Time
Verbal reasoning	~40–50	~17 min
Non-verbal reasoning	~40–50	~17 min

👉 Today we focus on Verbal Reasoning.

2️⃣ Types of Verbal Reasoning Questions

In SSB OIR, these 7 types are most common.

1. Series Completion

Find the next number or letter.

Example
2, 4, 8, 16, ?

Answer: 32

Pattern: multiply by 2.

2. Coding – Decoding

Example
If CAT = DBU, then DOG = ?

C → D
A → B
T → U

So
D → E
O → P
G → H

Answer: EPH

3. Odd One Out

Example
Cow, Dog, Tiger, Car

Answer: Car
Reason: others are animals.

4. Analogy

Example
Soldier : Army :: Student : ?

Answer: School

5. Blood Relations

Example
A is the son of B.
B is the sister of C.

What is C to A?

Answer: Parent

6. Direction Test

Example

Ravi walks

10 m north

5 m east

Where is he from start?

Answer: North-East

7. Alphabet Series

Example
A, C, E, G, ?

Answer: I

Pattern: skip one letter.

3️⃣ OIR Solving Strategy (Very Important)

🧠 Rule 1 – Speed matters more than difficulty
🧠 Rule 2 – Skip tough questions
🧠 Rule 3 – Solve in 10–15 seconds
🧠 Rule 4 – Never get stuck

SSB expects quick thinking officers.

4️⃣ Common Mistakes Aspirants Make

❌ Spending too much time on one question
❌ Trying to solve every question
❌ Panic due to time pressure

✅ Best candidates attempt 80–90% questions quickly.

